                <strong>Matthew Aslett</strong><br>
                <strong>ComputerBusinessRevieweOnline/Weblog June 23, 2006</strong>&nbsp;...No one ever  doubted Corel's business decision to support the new Office 12 formats, but it  does seems strange that a company that boasts &quot;we support more file  formats than anyone else, even Microsoft&quot; could not also find room for  ODF. It's a question of priorities, explained Carriere, who also maintained  that Corel would be there with ODF support as soon as customers demand it.  &quot;We focus our development on where we see demand,&quot; he said, &quot;If  and when this thing takes off, we'll be there and we'll be very proactive.&quot;... <a href="http://www.businessreviewonline.com/os/archives/2006/06/corel_sheds_lig.html">...Full  Story</a></p>
