              <p class="style2"><strong><a href="http://dot.kde.org/1149518002/" target="_hdl">KOffice 2.0, The Vision</a></strong><br>
                  <strong>Thomas Zander</strong><br>
                  <strong>KDE.News.org June 7, 2006</strong>&nbsp;KOffice is working on its future, one  based on KDE4. KOffice is starting new initiatives with libraries like Flake  and Pigment that are going to be used for all KOffice applications. For the  users of KOffice those changes are invisible until the 2.0 previews actually  start to appear some months from now. Therefore the KOffice crew wants to show  you their goals of what KOffice 2 is going to look like. Read more for the  whole story. <a href="http://dot.kde.org/1149518002/">...Full Story</a></p>
