                <strong>Paul Thurrott</strong><br>
                <strong>WindowsITPro May 29, 2006</strong>&nbsp;And speaking of Microsoft formats no one  was asking for, the software giant this week claimed that its Open XML formats,  used in the next version of Microsoft Office, offer better performance than the  open-source OpenDocument format. Take that, Linux fanboys!...I love the smell  of a format war in the morning. <a href="http://www.windowsitpro.com/Article/ArticleID/50419/50419.html">...Full Story</a></p>
