                <strong>John K. Waters</strong><br>
                <strong>Application Development Trends May 25, 2006</strong>&nbsp;A newly discovered  vulnerability in Microsoft Word XP and Word 2003 allows malicious hackers to  mount Trojan-based attacks through e-mail attachments, establishing a backdoor  that allows them to control compromised Windows PCs. According to security  experts, files containing the Mdropper-H and Backdoor-Ginwui Trojans have begun  to circulate on the Internet. <a href="http://www.adtmag.com/article.aspx?id=18605">...Full Story</a></p>
