                  <strong>Press Release</strong><br>
                  <strong>ITU.org June 18, 2006</strong>&nbsp;Geneva &mdash; A treaty agreement was signed today  at the conclusion of ITU&rsquo;s Regional Radiocommunication Conference (RRC-06) in  Geneva, heralding the development of &lsquo;all-digital&rsquo; terrestrial broadcast  services for sound and television. The digitalization of broadcasting in  Europe, Africa, Middle East and the Islamic Republic of Iran by 2015 represents  a major landmark towards establishing a more equitable, just and people-centred  Information Society. The digital switchover will leapfrog existing technologies  to connect the unconnected in underserved and remote communities and close the  digital divide. <a href="http://www.itu.int/newsroom/press_releases/2006/11.html">...Full Story</a></p>
