                  <strong>Press Release</strong><br>
                  <strong>CSRwire June 10, 2006</strong>&nbsp;The building of international consensus on  voluntary guidance to help organizations operate in a socially responsible way  made progress at the recent meeting of the ISO group that is developing the  future ISO 26000 standard on social responsibility. Some 320 people from 55  countries and 26 international organizations attended the third plenary meeting  of the ISO Working Group on Social Responsibility (WG SR) on 15-19 May 2006 in  Lisbon, Portugal. <a href="http://www.csrwire.com/article.cgi/5735.html">...Full  Story</a></p>
