                  <strong>ComuterWorld.dk June 2, 2006</strong>&nbsp;This article is in Danish, but Pamela  Jones at the <a href="http://www.groklaw.net/">Groklaw</a> home page today is  displaying the following summary in translation: [PJ: Groklaw member The_Pirate  sends us more news from Denmark, with his translation:] &quot;A majority in the  'Folketinget' (the Danish parliament) will Friday vote for introducing open  standards in the public sector, 'Computerworld' has learned. The vote is to be  taken when the politicians meet Friday, for the last time before the  parliament's lengthy summer vacation.&quot; <a href="http://www.computerworld.dk/art/34167?a=block&i=21">...Full Story</a></p>
